      "writtenOn": "2017-11-30T23:41:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, there\u0027s no great solution. The reason I put it here in TestPaths, rather than doing this in Paths was that I didn\u0027t want to require all users to have to call something at the beginning of main(), especially since using argv[0] is kind of gross anyway. \n\nAfter some more poking around, I tried `zx_object_get_property(zx_process_self(), ZX_PROP_NAME, name, sizeof(name))`. On device, if the binary\u0027s in /tmp, that returns \"/tmp/crashpad_test_test\" which looks OK! Unfortunately, kernel object names have a maximum length of ZX_MAX_NAME_LEN, and that\u0027s only 32, so it could very easily be truncated (and often is).\n\nI guess I\u0027ll implement Paths::Executable() like that for now, as that will work for now in Crashpad-standalone as long as the tree is very shallow, and try to plead my case again on ZX-797.",
